headline.main: NEW-YORK VOLUNTEERS.; Anniversary of the Surrender of the City of Mexico. Dinner at the Florence Hotel.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Anniversary of the Surrender of the City of Mexico-September 14, 1847--was celebrated in this City yesterday, in fine style, by the New-York Regiment of Volunteers.
docs.snippet: The Anniversary of the Surrender of the City of Mexico-September 14, 1847--was celebrated in this City yesterday, in fine style, by the New-York Regiment of Volunteers.

docs.lead_paragraph: ROBBERY OF A BANK-BOOK.--On Tuesday morning, a young man, named JOHN GIBSON. was arrested by Officer KEEFE, of he Chief's Office, upon a charge of grand larceny, in stealing a bank book from Mr. FRANCIS KINNER. NO. 10 Third Street.
